						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1278, Durmukhi, Māgha, śu. 10, Ma[ṅgaḷavāra]</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1357 January 31 Tuesday,</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Bukkaṇṇa-Voḍeya.</hi> It records that, under the orders of the king, his <hi rend="italic">Mahāpradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Maleya-Daṇṇāyaka</hi> made a gift of a new land, the old grant having been lost, for the service of the god <hi rend="bold">Śaṅkaranārāyaṇadēva.</hi> </p>						

